{
  "workflow": {
    "id": 15025,
    "name": "Post Google News headlines to Instagram images with GPT-4o-mini, PDF API Hub and Google Sheets",
    "views": 0,
    "recentViews": 0,
    "totalViews": 0,
    "createdAt": "2026-04-13T14:03:23.611Z",
    "description": "## Name\n\nAuto-post Google News to Instagram with OpenAI, PDF API Hub & Google Sheets\n\n## Description\n\nAutomatically fetch trending news from Google News RSS, rewrite headlines into viral captions with OpenAI, generate branded breaking-news images using PDF API Hub's HTML-to-Image API, and publish directly to Instagram — all tracked in a Google Sheet.\n\n## How it works\n\n- Every hour, the workflow pulls the latest articles from Google News RSS for your chosen topic\n- New articles are deduplicated against a Google Sheet to avoid reposting\n- OpenAI (GPT-4o-mini) rewrites the headline into a short, high-impact viral caption\n- PDF API Hub converts a branded HTML template into a mobile-format breaking-news image\n- The image is published to Instagram, and the Google Sheet row is updated with the image URL and marked as posted\n\n## Set up steps\n\n- Create a Google Sheet with a tab named `rss` and add the required column headers (~2 min). See the sticky note inside the workflow for the exact structure.\n- Connect your four credentials: Google Sheets OAuth2, OpenAI API, PDF API Hub API, and Instagram API (~5 min)\n- Set your news topic in the **Set Topic** node (e.g. `ai`, `crypto`, `sports`)\n- Optionally customize the HTML/CSS in the **Generate News Image** node to match your brand\n- Activate the workflow",
    "workflow": {
      "id": "fWrnscwHJE3q7A4d",
      "meta": {
        "instanceId": "277842713620d9f5554de3b1518b865a152c8c4db680008bd8aec536fc18b4a8"
      },
      "name": "Google News RSS → Clickbait → Image → Instagram (with Google Sheets Tracking)",
      "tags": [],
      "nodes": [
        {
          "id": "b7ae623d-7aee-4f22-99b3-9d37c13394dd",
          "name": "Sticky Note - Overview",
          "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
          "position": [
            -1136,
            496
          ],
          "parameters": {
            "color": 4,
            "width": 820,
            "height": 460,
            "content": "## 📰 Google News RSS → Clickbait → Image → Instagram\n\n**What this workflow does:**\n1. Fetches trending news from Google News RSS (configurable topic)\n2. Deduplicates against a Google Sheet so the same story isn't posted twice\n3. Rewrites the headline into a short, viral-style caption using OpenAI\n4. Generates a branded breaking-news image via PDF API Hub (HTML → Image)\n5. Publishes to Instagram and marks the row as posted\n\n**Before you start — set up your Google Sheet:**\nCreate a Google Sheet with a tab named `rss` and these column headers in row 1:\n\n| guid | title | pubDate | source | link | topic | media_url | is_posted | created_at | updated_at |\n\nLeave the rows empty — the workflow will populate them automatically.\n\n**Credentials needed:**\n- Google Sheets OAuth2\n- OpenAI API key\n- PDF API Hub API key (get one at pdfapihub.com)\n- Instagram API credentials"
          },
          "typeVersion": 1
        },
        {
          "id": "092cdbe8-f631-4334-960f-016d6d8163f3",
          "name": "Sticky Note - Image Generation",
          "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
          "position": [
            1440,
            336
          ],
          "parameters": {
            "color": 2,
            "width": 350,
            "height": 300,
            "content": "## 🖼️ Generate Image\n\nConverts the rewritten headline into a **branded breaking-news image** (375×812 mobile format) using PDF API Hub's HTML-to-Image API.\n\nThe HTML template includes:\n- BREAKING badge + LIVE indicator\n- Gradient dark background\n- The rewritten headline as the main text\n\n✏️ Customize the HTML/CSS in the node to match your brand colors, logo, and style."
          },
          "typeVersion": 1
        },
